### [1 Kings (1 Samuel) Chapter 8](../../../bib/kjv/sa1008.htm#001.md)

[1 Kings (1 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa1001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa1 8:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa1 8:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa1008.htm#001.md), By occasion of the ill
government of Samuel's sons, the Israelites ask a king; [Sa1
8:6](../../../bib/kjv/sa1008.htm#006.md), Samuel praying in grief, is
comforted by God; [Sa1 8:10](../../../bib/kjv/sa1008.htm#010.md), He tells
the manner of a king; [Sa1 8:19](../../../bib/kjv/sa1008.htm#019.md), God
wills Samuel to yield unto the importunity of the people.

